description:
In push.rs line 351, on a non-success response from the push endpoint, the full response body is read via response.text() without any size limit:

```rust
let body_text = response.text().await.unwrap_or_default();
tracing::debug!(account_id, status, body = %body_text, "push endpoint returned error");
```

A malicious push endpoint could return a multi-GB response body, causing OOM. The 30-second timeout provides some protection (~30GB at 1Gbps), but this is still a potential DoS vector.

The delivery client (delivery.rs) avoids this by only checking the status code and dropping the response.

Fix: either drop the response body (don't log it), or limit the read:
```rust
let body_text = response.text().await.unwrap_or_default();
let body_text: String = body_text.chars().take(1024).collect();
```

File: src/push.rs line 351
